The paper presents a methodology for using machine learning techniques to automatically discover unknown variable objects in large astronomical catalogs. The approach is based on a supervised algorithm, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB).
